00:31.039 --> 00:36.039
SUBTITLES BY EXPLOSIVESKULL

00:39.795 --> 00:42.533
[BELL TOLLING]

01:09.659 --> 01:10.991
WE'VE TALKED A LOT SO FAR

01:10.993 --> 01:14.594
ABOUT THE NATURE
OF GOOD STORYTELLING,

01:14.596 --> 01:18.398
BUT JUDGING FROM YOUR STORIES,
IT SEEMS LIKE A LOT OF YOU

01:18.400 --> 01:22.035
ARE JUST FLAPPING
IN THE WIND

01:22.037 --> 01:25.972
WITHOUT A VOICE,
AN INSTRUMENT.

01:25.974 --> 01:28.609
SO HOW DO WE CHANGE THAT?

01:28.611 --> 01:31.344
I KNOW I RESPOND
TO SOMETHING MORE REAL.

01:31.346 --> 01:33.446
MAYBE SOMETHING LIKE
A SPONTANEOUS OVERFLOW

01:33.448 --> 01:34.948
OF EMOTION.

01:34.950 --> 01:37.717
SPOKEN LIKE
A TRUE ROMANTIC.

01:37.719 --> 01:39.754
YOU GIVE ME
TOO MUCH CREDIT.

01:39.756 --> 01:42.323
NO, IF YOU'RE WRITING EMOTIONALLY,
YOU'RE WRITING SELFISHLY.

01:42.325 --> 01:44.491
YOU'RE NOT CONNECTING
WITH YOUR AUDIENCE.

01:44.493 --> 01:48.799
SO, READERS DON'T CONNECT
TO A STORY WITH SOUL?

01:50.832 --> 01:53.901
IS IT A WELL OUTLINED PLOT
YOU MOST RESPOND TO,

01:53.903 --> 01:58.609
OR EMOTION THAT REFLECTS
YOUR OWN HUMAN EXPERIENCE?

02:00.075 --> 02:03.978
WHAT MATTERS
IS WHERE IT COMES FROM.

02:03.980 --> 02:06.514
THAT IT COMES FROM YOU.

02:06.516 --> 02:08.749
THAT'S RIGHT.

02:08.751 --> 02:12.053
THAT IS RIGHT,
AND IN THAT WAY,

02:12.055 --> 02:15.523
THE BEST MOMENTS OF WRITING
ARE INSTINCTIVE,

02:15.525 --> 02:17.625
SHOWING WHO WE ARE,

02:17.627 --> 02:19.793
AND WHAT IT IS
WE'RE PROCESSING

02:19.795 --> 02:25.031
FROM A PLACE EACH OUR OWN.

02:25.033 --> 02:26.969
YOU UP FOR SHARING?

03:08.443 --> 03:11.578
THE CHURCH WAS SMALL,
BUT STRONG,

03:11.580 --> 03:13.447
RESTING ALONG THE LOW
COUNTRY BANKS

03:13.449 --> 03:15.382
WHERE MY FATHER
ONCE PREACHED.

03:15.384 --> 03:17.385
ON SUMMER MORNINGS
WE'D HAVE SUNDAY SCHOOL

03:17.387 --> 03:19.519
ALONGSIDE
THE COOLING CREEKS,

03:19.521 --> 03:21.388
LISTENING
TO BIBLE STORIES,

03:21.390 --> 03:23.990
AND SINGING ABOUT
THIS LITTLE LIGHT OF MINE.

03:23.992 --> 03:26.626
I'D SOMETIMES SNEAK AWAY,

03:26.628 --> 03:30.764
BRAVING THE GOLD AND GREEN
MARSH GRASS UP TO MY NECK,

03:30.766 --> 03:34.034
SOFT SUN PEAKING THROUGH
PATCHES OF SPANISH MOSS,

03:34.036 --> 03:36.605
HEAT AND LIGHT UPON MY FACE...

03:39.008 --> 03:40.877
WHAT I IMAGINED GOD FELT LIKE.

03:44.413 --> 03:46.780
BUT AS THE TIDES MOVED OUT,

03:46.782 --> 03:50.785
THAT SUN SHRUNK AWAY

03:50.787 --> 03:53.887
ON THE JOURNEY

03:53.889 --> 03:55.691
OF A SINGLE DAY.

04:08.069 --> 04:10.171
♪ HERE I COME AGAIN,
NOW, BABY ♪

04:10.173 --> 04:14.841
♪ LIKE A DOG IN HEAT ♪

04:14.843 --> 04:17.844
♪ TELL IT'S ME
BY THE CLAMOR, NOW, BABY ♪

04:17.846 --> 04:21.014
♪ I LIKE TO TEAR UP
THE STREET ♪

04:21.016 --> 04:24.618
♪ NOW, I BEEN SMOKIN'
FOR SO LONG ♪

04:24.620 --> 04:27.921
♪ YA KNOW I'M HERE TO STAY ♪

04:27.923 --> 04:31.125
♪ GOT YOU IN
A STRANGLEHOLD, BABY ♪

04:31.127 --> 04:33.430
♪ YOU BEST GET
OUTTA MY WAY ♪

04:47.175 --> 04:50.844
♪ THE ROAD I CRUISE
IS A BITCH, NOW, BABY ♪

04:50.846 --> 04:54.014
♪ YOU KNOW YOU CAN'T
TURN ME ROUND ♪

04:54.016 --> 04:57.517
♪ AND IF A HOUSE
GETS IN MY WAY, BABY ♪

04:57.519 --> 05:00.855
♪ YA KNOW
I'LL BURN IT DOWN ♪

05:00.857 --> 05:03.990
♪ REMEMBER THE NIGHT
THAT YOU LEFT ME? ♪

05:03.992 --> 05:07.260
♪ YOU PUT ME IN MY PLACE ♪

05:07.262 --> 05:10.598
♪ GOT YOU IN
A STRANGLEHOLD, BABY ♪

05:10.600 --> 05:13.637
♪ YOU BETTER TRUST
YOUR FATE ♪

05:44.634 --> 05:47.166
HEY, YOU BOYS WANT SOME OF
THIS WHILE I GOT IT OUT?

05:47.168 --> 05:48.868
WHY DON'T YOU SHUT
THE HELL UP?

05:48.870 --> 05:51.137
WHOO!

05:51.139 --> 05:52.805
YOU READY?

05:52.807 --> 05:54.711
KEEP YOUR PANTIES ON.

05:56.312 --> 05:58.211
HEY!

05:58.213 --> 06:00.813
PICK YOU UP AT 10?

06:00.815 --> 06:01.951
YEAH.

06:04.153 --> 06:06.286
YOU'LL BE THERE, RIGHT?

06:06.288 --> 06:08.154
- YEAH.
- HMM, YEAH?

06:08.156 --> 06:09.990
'CAUSE WE NEED YOU.

06:09.992 --> 06:11.261
SHIT.

06:14.663 --> 06:16.897
10.

06:16.899 --> 06:20.166
HE'D BEEN A FRIEND
SINCE SEVENTH GRADE.

06:20.168 --> 06:23.173
BUT MY MOM RETURNED US TO THESE
WATERWAYS OF HER FAMILY.

06:24.607 --> 06:26.173
I GOT CAUGHT CRYING
IN A HALLWAY,

06:26.175 --> 06:28.608
AND HE CHASED THE OTHER
KIDS AWAY AS THEY LAUGHED.

06:28.610 --> 06:31.678
BYE, JOSEPH! WHOO!

06:31.680 --> 06:35.519
A WARRIOR
SUDDENLY AT MY SIDE.

06:38.086 --> 06:40.988
MOST OF THE TIME
I SHUT MYSELF OFF,

06:40.990 --> 06:44.959
DRIFTING BACK
INTO A DARK CLOUD,

06:44.961 --> 06:47.760
A SLOW FALL.

06:47.762 --> 06:50.831
THEY CALLED IT DEPRESSION

06:50.833 --> 06:55.034
AND ASKED IF I WAS HAVING
THOUGHTS ABOUT SUICIDE.

06:55.036 --> 06:58.207
I LIED AND SAID NO.

07:06.983 --> 07:08.685
WHERE YOU BEEN?

07:10.653 --> 07:11.987
NOWHERE.

07:15.658 --> 07:17.259
ALLISON CALLED.

07:19.995 --> 07:21.597
THEY SAID YOU SHOULD
BE THERE BY 8.

07:31.973 --> 07:35.009
THE PAIN IS A CURSE

07:35.011 --> 07:37.844
HANDED DOWN FROM MY FATHER...

07:37.846 --> 07:41.014
LET'S REMEMBER, AS THE BREAD
NOURISHES OUR BODIES AND OUR MINDS,

07:41.016 --> 07:44.853
LET IT NOURISH YOUR SOUL
AND YOUR FAITH.

07:48.024 --> 07:50.894
LOOKING FOR SOMETHING
HE'D NEVER FIND.

08:01.870 --> 08:07.074
BUT AT TIMES, THE PAIN EXPLODES
OUT OF MY MIND AND HAND.

08:07.076 --> 08:08.778
A SWEET RELEASE.

08:20.790 --> 08:23.057
- WHAT UP?
- NOTHING.

08:23.059 --> 08:25.759
I BET YOU $1.99

08:25.761 --> 08:27.330
YOU AIN'T GOT OFF
THAT DAMN COUCH ALL DAY.

08:32.967 --> 08:34.303
ASSHOLE.

08:49.118 --> 08:50.917
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- NOTHING.

08:50.919 --> 08:52.219
- WHAT DID YOU TAKE?
- IT'S NOTHING.

08:52.221 --> 08:54.854
- DICK, GIVE IT BACK!
- [LAUGHING]

08:54.856 --> 08:57.925
I'M GONNA KICK
YOUR ASS, HOWARD!

08:57.927 --> 08:59.026
RIGHT.

08:59.028 --> 09:01.031
YOU AIN'T GONNA DO SHIT.

09:02.932 --> 09:03.964
[HOWARD YELPS]

09:03.966 --> 09:08.134
♪ I'VE GOT DREAMS ♪

09:08.136 --> 09:12.708
♪ DREAMS TO REMEMBER ♪

09:15.745 --> 09:18.344
JOSEPH, COME IN.

09:18.346 --> 09:22.281
♪ DREAMS TO REMEMBER ♪

09:22.283 --> 09:24.852
YOU ALL KNOW JOSEPH,
CHARLIE'S LITTLE BROTHER.

09:24.854 --> 09:27.286
YEAH, WHAT'S UP?

09:27.288 --> 09:29.759
COME TO DRINK
ALL OUR BEER AND SPLIT?

09:34.996 --> 09:36.796
WHERE'S CHARLIE?

09:36.798 --> 09:38.265
HE'S IN THE STUDY.

09:38.267 --> 09:41.068
GO FIND HIM.
HE'S BEEN LOOKING FOR YA.

09:41.070 --> 09:44.338
♪ ALL I KNOW
WALKED AWAY AND CRASHED ♪

09:44.340 --> 09:46.406
♪ I'VE GOT DREAMS ♪

09:46.408 --> 09:48.175
QUITE THE CHARMER.

09:48.177 --> 09:49.879
LET HIM BE.

09:53.381 --> 09:57.117
- ♪ I'VE GOT DREAMS ♪
- ♪ ROUGH DREAMS ♪

09:57.119 --> 10:01.088
♪ DREAMS TO REMEMBER ♪

10:01.090 --> 10:02.388
THE ONLY THING
THAT CONFUSES ME

10:02.390 --> 10:05.526
IS HOW YOU GOT
AN INVITE TO MY PARTY.

10:05.528 --> 10:07.297
JOSEPH.

10:10.198 --> 10:12.498
HOW YOU DOIN', BUDDY?

10:12.500 --> 10:15.169
I'M ALL RIGHT.

10:15.171 --> 10:18.272
STAYING IN TROUBLE?

10:18.274 --> 10:19.473
NO.

10:19.475 --> 10:21.241
OH, BULLSHIT.

10:21.243 --> 10:22.943
HEY, LET ME GO SAY HEY
TO SOME PEOPLE.

10:22.945 --> 10:24.978
I'LL CATCH UP WITH YOU
IN A SEC, OKAY?

10:24.980 --> 10:26.349
ALL RIGHT.

10:28.884 --> 10:30.854
WHERE'S MY WIFE?

10:32.254 --> 10:35.055
[JOSEPH]
CHARLIE WAS MY HALF BROTHER,

10:35.057 --> 10:38.858
ABANDONED BY MY FATHER
WHEN HE WAS 10.

10:38.860 --> 10:42.429
HE MADE GOOD
BY BEING HIMSELF,

10:42.431 --> 10:45.168
A WIDE SPACE
BETWEEN HIM AND ME.

11:06.455 --> 11:10.126
♪ I STILL LOVE YOU ANYWAY ♪

11:12.293 --> 11:16.162
♪ I DON'T WANT YOU
TO EVER LEAVE ♪

11:16.164 --> 11:20.334
♪ GIRL, YOU JUST SATISFY ME ♪

11:20.336 --> 11:23.871
THAT'S TRUE.
IT'S NOT... IT'S NOT BAD.

11:23.873 --> 11:25.939
YOU SEEM TO HAVE ALL
THE ANSWERS, DON'T YOU?

11:25.941 --> 11:27.608
I'M NOT SAYING I HAVE
ALL THE ANSWERS,

11:27.610 --> 11:30.209
BUT WE'VE ALL HAD
THOSE MOMENTS THAT FEEL RIGHT,

11:30.211 --> 11:32.079
WHERE WE FEEL LIKE
WE'RE AT OUR BEST,

11:32.081 --> 11:36.116
WHERE WE'RE NOT BOGGED DOWN
WITH SELF DOUBT OR FEAR.

11:36.118 --> 11:39.585
YOU KNOW, WHERE WE TRUST
IN THE WORLD AROUND US.

11:39.587 --> 11:42.289
- WHICH IS WHAT?
- FAITH.

11:42.291 --> 11:45.559
STRIVING FOR SOME
SENSE OF HOPE, OF PEACE.

11:45.561 --> 11:48.094
OKAY, THE EAGLE SOARING
THROUGH THE AIR ACHIEVES

11:48.096 --> 11:49.563
BECAUSE OF THREE THINGS...

11:49.565 --> 11:55.035
HIS WINGS, THE WIND,
AND HIS FAITH IN BOTH.

11:55.037 --> 11:58.037
ALL RIGHT, OUR ROLE IS
TO ACCEPT THAT WHO WE ARE

11:58.039 --> 11:59.605
IS ABSOLUTELY
INTEGRAL TO THAT,

11:59.607 --> 12:03.209
AND STOP FIGHTING AGAINST
THIS CONCEPT OF OUR VALUE.

12:03.211 --> 12:05.177
AND TO RECOGNIZE
THAT THE WORLD CANNOT BE

12:05.179 --> 12:08.949
WHAT IT'S DETERMINED TO BE
WITHOUT US AS WE ARE.

12:08.951 --> 12:11.384
WHAT DID YOU THINK, JOE?

12:11.386 --> 12:13.587
I LIKED IT.

12:13.589 --> 12:16.055
SEE THERE? THERE YOU GO.

12:16.057 --> 12:17.590
YOUTH OF AMERICA LIKES IT.

12:17.592 --> 12:22.061
[MUSIC PLAYING]

12:22.063 --> 12:24.297
[CHUCKLING]

12:24.299 --> 12:26.134
[POUNDING AT DOOR]

12:29.504 --> 12:31.106
[POUNDING CONTINUES]

12:35.644 --> 12:37.246
YEAH?

12:39.248 --> 12:41.714
WHAT THE HELL
YOU DOING IN HERE?

12:41.716 --> 12:42.918
NOTHING.

12:52.327 --> 12:54.429
CAR'S IN MY WAY.

12:55.965 --> 12:58.434
FINE. I HAD TO GET
JAY ANYWAY.

13:09.144 --> 13:11.210
YOU BEST GET TO CLEANING
THIS PLACE OUT

13:11.212 --> 13:14.748
- LIKE I KEEP TELLING YOU.
- YEAH, WHATEVER.

13:14.750 --> 13:18.384
WHAT THE HELL DID YOU SAY?

13:18.386 --> 13:21.722
YOU LIVE HERE FOR FREE.
BARELY GOT OUTTA HIGH SCHOOL.

13:21.724 --> 13:26.059
HELL, YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE
A GODDAMN JOB.

13:26.061 --> 13:29.365
YOU STARTIN' TO AMOUNT
TO JACK SHIT, YOU KNOW THAT?

13:32.768 --> 13:35.538
I DON'T KNOW WHY YOU ALWAYS
GIVE ME SUCH A HARD TIME.

13:38.673 --> 13:41.944
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT A HARD TIME IS.

13:53.455 --> 13:55.557
[MUSIC PLAYING]

14:06.434 --> 14:10.570
HOW IS YOUR MOM DOING?

14:10.572 --> 14:14.141
- SHE'S OKAY.
- GOOD.

14:14.143 --> 14:16.675
DO YOU WANT SOME OF THIS?

14:16.677 --> 14:19.345
YEAH, SURE.

14:19.347 --> 14:23.552
SO, ARE YOU STILL
THINKING ABOUT SCHOOL?

14:26.587 --> 14:29.689
WHO SAID I WAS
THINKING ABOUT SCHOOL?

14:29.691 --> 14:31.690
CHARLIE.

14:31.692 --> 14:34.661
YOU SHOULD, YOU KNOW?

14:34.663 --> 14:36.399
YOU'D DO WELL.

14:42.071 --> 14:45.504
♪ TOOK MY DADDY
FOR GRANTED ♪

14:45.506 --> 14:50.076
♪ YOU KNOW I PLAYED HIM
FOR A FOOL ♪

14:50.078 --> 14:54.214
♪ FOUND OUT LATER
THAT I LOVE HIM SO ♪

14:54.216 --> 14:57.687
♪ AFTER BREAKING LOVE'S
GOLDEN RULE ♪

15:00.688 --> 15:04.623
♪ I MAY BE WRONG,
BUT WE CAN GET ALONG ♪

15:04.625 --> 15:08.661
♪ AND I'M GOING BACK
WHERE I BELONG ♪

15:08.663 --> 15:13.400
♪ YOU KNOW I'M GOING BACK
WHERE I BELONG ♪

15:13.402 --> 15:16.236
♪ I SAID I'M GOING BACK ♪

15:16.238 --> 15:22.245
♪ MMM, I'M GOING BACK
WHERE I BELONG ♪

15:27.649 --> 15:30.617
I WAS ALONE,

15:30.619 --> 15:33.056
BUT I WOULD ON OCCASION
TAKE COMPANY IN OTHER FOLKS.

15:35.691 --> 15:40.193
NOT THROUGH EASY CONVERSATION
OR EYE CONTACT.

15:40.195 --> 15:42.896
INSTEAD, I'D MAKE UP
STORIES ABOUT THEM,

15:42.898 --> 15:47.702
WHERE THEY CAME FROM,
BASED ON A SIDEWAYS GLANCE...

15:49.538 --> 15:52.508
OR THAT NIGHT,
A LITTLE MORE.

16:12.293 --> 16:13.663
HOW'S IT GOING?

16:16.932 --> 16:18.500
ALL RIGHT.

16:21.602 --> 16:23.505
YOU FROM AROUND HERE?

16:27.275 --> 16:29.508
YEAH.

16:29.510 --> 16:32.411
YOU?

16:32.413 --> 16:34.182
NOT FAR.

16:47.763 --> 16:50.199
YOUR DADDY A PREACHER?

16:51.866 --> 16:53.568
YEAH.

16:56.370 --> 16:58.305
YEAH.

16:58.307 --> 17:01.541
YOU GOT THE HEAD
OF A PREACHER.

17:01.543 --> 17:04.611
THEY WAY IT CURVES WIDE.

17:04.613 --> 17:06.382
HMM.

17:16.424 --> 17:18.461
THE HOLY SPIRIT...

17:21.296 --> 17:23.231
IT LEFT ITS MARK ON YOU.

17:25.467 --> 17:27.901
THE EYE OF GOD...

17:27.903 --> 17:30.405
THERE.

17:32.740 --> 17:37.244
YOU USE THAT SIGHT,

17:37.246 --> 17:39.248
YOU'LL FIND YOUR WAY.

18:02.336 --> 18:04.606
BEST GET TO IT.

18:08.410 --> 18:12.011
I SAW SOMETHING THERE...

18:12.013 --> 18:13.848
A LIGHT.

18:15.817 --> 18:19.322
AN IDEA THAT WOULD LATER
LIVE AND BREATHE...

18:21.355 --> 18:23.826
FORMING LIKE THE CREST
OF A BREAKING WAVE.

18:25.961 --> 18:28.998
A REFLECTION
OF WHAT FLOATS INSIDE.

18:37.306 --> 18:39.939
- FINALLY.
- HMM.

18:39.941 --> 18:41.844
[CHUCKLING]

18:52.054 --> 18:54.019
[COUGHING]

18:54.021 --> 18:57.393
- EASY THERE, TIGER.
- MMM-MMM.

19:00.996 --> 19:02.898
WE GOTTA GET READY SOON.

19:04.833 --> 19:07.801
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

19:07.803 --> 19:10.036
PAY ATTENTION...

19:10.038 --> 19:11.738
AND WE'LL GET PAID.

19:11.740 --> 19:15.342
♪ IT'S SUMMERTIME ♪

19:15.344 --> 19:17.811
[HOWARD] YOU KNOW MY
COUSIN DOWN IN OCRACOKE.

19:17.813 --> 19:19.712
YEAH, HE'S LOUSY
WHEN IT COMES TO DRINKING,

19:19.714 --> 19:23.016
BUT HE SNIFFS OUT
THE HOT SPOTS.

19:23.018 --> 19:26.819
♪ I'M THE KIND
THAT MOVES ON ♪

19:26.821 --> 19:30.457
♪ YOUR DADDY'S RICH ♪

19:30.459 --> 19:32.359
[HOWARD] TOLD ME ABOUT
A LITTLE JUKE JOINT

19:32.361 --> 19:35.495
AROUND THE ISLAND
HE'D BEEN FREQUENTING,

19:35.497 --> 19:39.535
AND WHAT HAPPENED ONE NIGHT WHEN
THEY WAS ALL DRUNK AS HELL.

19:46.907 --> 19:51.643
AND SOME SERIOUS SMOOTHNESS
SHOWED UP WITH A PLAN.

19:51.645 --> 19:54.948
♪ THEN YOU'LL
SPREAD YOUR WINGS ♪

19:54.950 --> 19:57.385
♪ AND YOU'LL TAKE
TO THE SKY ♪

19:59.421 --> 20:02.956
♪ BUT TILL THAT MORNING ♪

20:02.958 --> 20:06.362
♪ THERE AIN'T NOTHIN'
GONNA HARM YOU ♪

20:07.828 --> 20:13.435
♪ YOU GOT YOUR DADDY
AND MOMMY STANDIN' BY ♪

20:32.053 --> 20:35.121
TAX TIME, BABY!
LET'S GO!

20:35.123 --> 20:37.423
[HOWARD] THESE THREE DUDES
COME IN WITH SHOTGUNS

20:37.425 --> 20:38.924
HOLDING THE PLACE UP.

20:38.926 --> 20:41.661
ONE TOOK ON A CASH BOX,
GETTIN' IT ALL EMPTIED OUT.

20:41.663 --> 20:43.630
THE OTHER TWO WATCHED
THE CROWD MAKING SURE

20:43.632 --> 20:47.633
SOME HILLBILLY
DON'T PLAY VIGILANTE.

20:47.635 --> 20:50.839
ANYTHING COME UP,
THEY ALL GET THE HELL OUT.

20:52.207 --> 20:54.073
AND BY THE TIME ANYONE
WAS SOBER ENOUGH

20:54.075 --> 20:56.776
TO REALIZE WHAT THE HELL
WAS HAPPENING,

20:56.778 --> 21:00.078
THEY WAS LONG GONE.

21:00.080 --> 21:03.682
TURNS OUT THEY'VE BEEN HITTING
JOINTS ALL OVER THE COAST,

21:03.684 --> 21:05.718
STEALING DRUNK FOLKS' MONEY
WHILE THEY WAS TOO DRUNK

21:05.720 --> 21:07.653
TO DO ANYTHING ABOUT IT.

21:07.655 --> 21:10.923
AND THOSE FOLKS SURE AS HELL
WON'T CALL IN THE POKEY.

21:10.925 --> 21:12.659
HELL, THEY'D BUST UP
THE STILLS

21:12.661 --> 21:14.460
AND SHUT HER DOWN
IN TWO SHAKES.

21:14.462 --> 21:16.766
WOULDN'T GIVE
A RAT'S ASS PAST THAT.

21:21.736 --> 21:25.004
SO, THEY JUST KEPT
ON MOVING,

21:25.006 --> 21:28.177
HIDING IN THE BANKS,
THE CRANNIES.

21:30.045 --> 21:35.248
ALL ANYBODY KNEW WAS
IT WAS THREE BLACK FELLAS,

21:35.250 --> 21:37.650
SMART AS HELL,

21:37.652 --> 21:39.755
QUIET AS A PACK
OF CHURCH MICE.

21:42.958 --> 21:44.724
LEGENDS.

21:44.726 --> 21:49.799
♪ NOW, HUSH, LITTLE BABY,
DON'T YOU CRY ♪

21:52.701 --> 21:58.507
♪ YOU JUST HUSH, LITTLE BABY,
AND DON'T YOU CRY ♪

22:09.116 --> 22:12.885
[SNIFFING]

22:12.887 --> 22:16.055
- IT SMELLS LIKE PUSSY.
- MM-HMM.

22:16.057 --> 22:18.257
[LAUGHING, COUGHING]

22:18.259 --> 22:19.859
THIS SHIT'S SERIOUS, MAN.

22:19.861 --> 22:21.864
WHAT, YOU THINK
I DON'T KNOW THAT?

22:29.270 --> 22:30.839
AIN'T GONNA DO JACK SHIT.

22:35.609 --> 22:36.910
HOW MUCH YOU THINK
WE'D GET?

22:36.912 --> 22:38.881
ENOUGH.

22:42.784 --> 22:47.786
MY MAN.

22:47.788 --> 22:49.692
UH, UH, UH, UH!

22:50.692 --> 22:52.126
WHAT?

23:00.134 --> 23:03.068
[HOWARD]
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

23:03.070 --> 23:04.336
YOU LOOK FUNNY.

23:04.338 --> 23:06.608
[LAUGHING]
YEAH?

23:08.242 --> 23:10.943
WELL, HUCKLEBERRY HERE
IS GONNA SAVE YOUR ASS.

23:10.945 --> 23:13.645
- SHIT.
- SHIT, NOTHIN'.

23:13.647 --> 23:16.751
SICK AND TIRED OF BUSTING
MY ASS TO BUY A SIX PACK.

23:18.853 --> 23:20.256
ABOUT TO CHANGE THAT SHIT.

23:29.263 --> 23:30.565
BE A MAN ABOUT IT.

23:32.968 --> 23:37.202
PUFF IT OUT A LITTLE BIT.

23:37.204 --> 23:40.174
- ESPECIALLY YOU.
- HMM?

23:41.776 --> 23:44.643
THAT SHIT YOU WRITE.

23:44.645 --> 23:46.179
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.

23:46.181 --> 23:48.280
I SEE WHAT YOU DO.

23:48.282 --> 23:53.621
YOU DON'T WANNA TELL ME,
AIN'T NO SKIN OFF MY ASS.

23:57.826 --> 24:02.728
FOLKS LOOK AT ME,
THEY LOOK AT MY POPS,

24:02.730 --> 24:05.632
AND THEY FIGURE THAT'S
ALL THEY EVER GONNA GET,

24:05.634 --> 24:11.371
A PUNK-ASS BRAWLER.

24:11.373 --> 24:14.974
BUT YOU...

24:14.976 --> 24:16.779
YOU'RE DIFFERENT.

24:19.079 --> 24:22.148
♪ HOW COULD IT ALL
GO WRONG ♪

24:22.150 --> 24:26.753
♪ YOU KNOW IT HURTS ME
DEEP INSIDE ♪

24:26.755 --> 24:30.890
♪ FEEL I'VE BEEN TAKEN
FOR A RIDE ♪

24:30.892 --> 24:33.359
♪ I GOT NOTHIN' LEFT TO HIDE ♪

24:33.361 --> 24:35.164
STEP IT UP, JACK.

24:36.730 --> 24:38.067
HMM?

24:52.113 --> 24:54.980
[JOSEPH] WE WEREN'T
GONNA HURT ANYONE.

24:54.982 --> 24:57.784
GUN WASN'T EVEN LOADED.

24:57.786 --> 25:00.719
COURAGE WAS HIS WEAPON.

25:00.721 --> 25:02.657
LET'S GO.

25:23.144 --> 25:24.947
[MAN BELCHES]

25:38.259 --> 25:40.128
PERFECT.

25:47.801 --> 25:50.772
I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T KNOW, MAN.

25:53.107 --> 25:56.109
LOOK, NO SECOND THOUGHTS.
JUST GET IN THERE AND DO IT.

25:56.111 --> 25:58.478
TWO MINUTES FROM NOW
WE'RE GONNA BE ON OUR WAY.

25:58.480 --> 26:01.016
[BREATHING LOUDLY]

26:05.019 --> 26:06.422
PUT 'EM ON.

26:08.021 --> 26:12.827
♪ I'M GOIN' WHERE
THE COLD WIND GOES ♪

26:18.133 --> 26:21.234
♪ WHERE THE SUN
DON'T EVER SHINE ♪

26:21.236 --> 26:25.841
♪ I'LL BE SHIVERING
THE WHOLE NIGHT THROUGH ♪

26:27.976 --> 26:33.782
♪ MY GIRL,
DON'T YOU LIE TO ME ♪

26:35.250 --> 26:36.484
DON'T MOVE!

26:42.156 --> 26:43.391
FILL IT!

26:45.226 --> 26:46.361
GOD DAMN IT!

26:49.196 --> 26:51.132
COME ON!

26:57.404 --> 27:00.139
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

27:00.141 --> 27:01.777
THAT'S IT.

27:12.487 --> 27:15.287
WHAT THE HELL?

27:15.289 --> 27:18.124
I'M SORRY.

27:39.213 --> 27:41.847
IF ANYBODY ASKS,

27:41.849 --> 27:44.952
THE NAME'S LEROY.

27:56.530 --> 27:58.866
COME ON! COME ON!
COME ON!

28:00.500 --> 28:02.270
[HOWARD LAUGHING]

28:07.008 --> 28:09.144
[BREATHING LOUDLY]

28:15.115 --> 28:20.952
♪ BLACK ♪

28:20.954 --> 28:26.928
♪ IS THE COLOR
OF MY TRUE LOVE'S HAIR ♪

28:30.064 --> 28:36.038
♪ HIS FACE SO SOFT
AND WONDROUS PALE ♪

28:40.407 --> 28:46.280
♪ THE PUREST EYES ♪

28:49.517 --> 28:54.022
♪ AND THE STRONGEST HANDS ♪

28:56.990 --> 29:02.029
♪ I LOVE THE GROUND
ON WHERE HE STANDS ♪

29:04.097 --> 29:09.303
♪ I LOVE THE GROUND
ON WHERE HE STANDS ♪

29:12.440 --> 29:18.447
♪ BLACK ♪

29:20.347 --> 29:26.518
♪ IS THE COLOR ♪

29:26.520 --> 29:29.957
♪ OF MY TRUE LOVE'S HAIR ♪

29:32.226 --> 29:37.633
♪ OF MY TRUE LOVE'S HAIR ♪

29:39.567 --> 29:45.470
♪ OF MY TRUE ♪

29:45.472 --> 29:47.675
♪ LOVE'S HAIR ♪

30:03.124 --> 30:07.559
♪ OH, I LOVE ♪

30:07.561 --> 30:09.628
♪ MY LOVER ♪

30:09.630 --> 30:13.468
♪ AND WELL HE KNOWS ♪

30:16.471 --> 30:22.477
♪ YES, I LOVE THE GROUND
ON WHERE HE GOES ♪

30:24.077 --> 30:28.646
♪ AND STILL I HOPE ♪

30:28.648 --> 30:34.055
♪ THAT THE TIME WILL COME ♪

30:35.323 --> 30:40.558
♪ WHEN HE AND I
WILL BE AS ONE ♪

30:40.560 --> 30:45.663
♪ WHEN HE AND I
WILL BE AS ONE ♪

30:45.665 --> 30:50.304
♪ WHEN HE AND I
WILL BE AS ONE ♪

30:52.306 --> 30:58.145
♪ OH, BLACK ♪

30:59.380 --> 31:05.284
♪ IS THE COLOR ♪

31:05.286 --> 31:08.690
♪ OF MY TRUE LOVE'S HAIR ♪

31:10.625 --> 31:14.395
♪ OF MY TRUE LOVE'S HAIR ♪

31:17.731 --> 31:22.234
♪ OF MY TRUE ♪

31:22.236 --> 31:26.742
♪ LOVE'S HAIR ♪

31:28.509 --> 31:30.412
[GUNSHOT]

31:43.391 --> 31:45.594
THAT'S YOUR MEMORY?

31:50.664 --> 31:52.134
AND NOW?

31:57.137 --> 32:00.408
I KNOW WHAT IT FEELS LIKE
TO BE DEPRESSED.

32:02.710 --> 32:07.345
MM-HMM, BUT YOU HAVE SOMETHING
HE PROBABLY DIDN'T HAVE.

32:07.347 --> 32:09.681
WHAT'S THAT?

32:09.683 --> 32:11.420
YOUR IMAGINATION.

32:24.164 --> 32:28.133
[JOSEPH] IN RESPONSE TO THIS
MEMORY, A STORY CAME TO ME

32:28.135 --> 32:32.438
OF A QUIET MAN
WITH UNSEEN STRENGTH.

32:32.440 --> 32:35.908
HIS HORN, HIS VOICE,

32:35.910 --> 32:40.478
LIKE THE SONG
THAT CAME FROM ME...

32:40.480 --> 32:42.748
SEEKING A HOME,

32:42.750 --> 32:45.086
A PLACE IN THIS WORLD.

32:52.259 --> 32:54.392
HOLY, SHIT!

32:54.394 --> 32:56.828
DUDE, THERE'S LIKE
A THOUSAND BUCKS BACK HERE!

32:56.830 --> 32:58.863
SEE, WHAT DID I TELL YOU, HUH?

32:58.865 --> 33:00.732
MAYBE YOU AIN'T SUCH
A DUMB-ASS AFTER ALL.

33:00.734 --> 33:02.535
- WHOO!
- [LAUGHING]

33:02.537 --> 33:04.769
THAT WAS MESSED UP
WHEN THAT GUY PULLED THAT GUN.

33:04.771 --> 33:06.575
THAT FREAKED ME OUT.

33:10.944 --> 33:13.414
YOU SAW IT HAPPEN,
DIDN'T YA?

33:16.183 --> 33:17.549
LOOK, MAN,
YOU GOTTA SPEAK UP.

33:17.551 --> 33:20.355
ALL RIGHT, THAT COULD
HAVE BEEN BAD.

33:24.525 --> 33:26.725
WHOA-HA-HA-HA-HA!

33:26.727 --> 33:29.694
♪ LOOK AWAY, LOOK AWAY ♪

33:29.696 --> 33:34.299
♪ MY FATHER ONCE DID ♪

33:34.301 --> 33:37.304
♪ GO AWAY TO RETURN ♪

33:39.240 --> 33:41.675
GOOD, HE'S HERE.

33:51.986 --> 33:53.651
[ALAN]
RUSTY!

33:53.653 --> 33:56.223
- THIS PLACE IS A DUMP.
- A FUCKIN' RAGER.

33:57.258 --> 33:58.556
RUSTY?

33:58.558 --> 34:01.427
- HE'S SLEEPING.
- NO SHIT.

34:01.429 --> 34:03.394
[RUSTY SNORING]

34:03.396 --> 34:05.232
OH, WHAT'S THAT SMELL?

34:07.401 --> 34:08.632
I THINK IT'S PISS.

34:08.635 --> 34:11.873
RUST! RUSTY!

34:14.242 --> 34:15.306
[CHUCKLING]

34:15.309 --> 34:16.541
IS HE ALIVE?

34:16.543 --> 34:17.913
[SNORING]

34:18.945 --> 34:20.614
- TWO.
- THREE.

34:22.516 --> 34:23.815
I GOT IT.

34:23.818 --> 34:26.784
WHAT UP, BUDDY?

34:26.786 --> 34:29.857
YEAH, TAKE A SHOWER,
YOU STINK-ASS!

34:32.693 --> 34:34.963
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU GUYS?

34:39.500 --> 34:41.431
HOW THE HELL YOU BEEN?

34:41.434 --> 34:43.434
GOOD.

34:43.436 --> 34:45.574
I'M GOOD, YOU KNOW.

34:47.440 --> 34:50.376
YOU PACKIN'?

34:50.378 --> 34:53.411
MAN, THAT BETTER NOT BE
THE ONLY REASON

34:53.414 --> 34:57.682
YOU COME TO SEE ME.

34:57.684 --> 35:01.287
OF COURSE, IT AIN'T.
I LOVE ME SOME RUSSELL.

35:01.289 --> 35:04.289
YEAH, RIGHT.

35:04.291 --> 35:05.492
WHAT YOU GOT?

35:11.998 --> 35:14.066
YOU'LL LIKE THIS.

35:14.068 --> 35:16.271
GOOD STUFF?

35:17.070 --> 35:20.338
IT'S THE TWO F'S OF "STUFF."

35:20.340 --> 35:22.608
GET YOUR FEET OFF MY COUCH.

35:22.610 --> 35:26.311
HELL, YEAH!
LOOK, IT'S OVER AN OUNCE.

35:26.313 --> 35:29.615
ONLY 'CAUSE YOUR BOY HERE
IS SUCH A BAD-ASS.

35:29.617 --> 35:32.383
USUALLY, THERE'S
A CEILING ON THIS SHIT.

35:32.385 --> 35:34.889
OUNCE OF THAT SHIT, TOO.

35:36.090 --> 35:37.956
SURE YOU GOT THIS
KINDA DOUGH?

35:37.958 --> 35:40.829
YEAH, I'VE BEEN WORKING.

35:43.364 --> 35:45.930
HEY, DO YOU STILL HANG OUT
WITH THAT CHICK?

35:45.932 --> 35:47.700
WHAT'S HER NAME?

35:47.702 --> 35:49.501
- LYDIA.
- YEAH, THAT'S IT.

35:49.503 --> 35:51.637
YOU ALL STILL TALK?

35:51.639 --> 35:54.572
- NO, IT'S BEEN A WHILE.
- SMART MOVE, MAN.

35:54.574 --> 35:56.742
THAT CHICK...

35:56.744 --> 35:58.610
SHE GOT ELEPHANTITIS
AND SHIT.

35:58.612 --> 36:02.613
- THAT'S WHAT I SAID.
- YEAH? SHE AIN'T THAT BAD.

36:02.615 --> 36:05.583
HER BELLY BUTTON'S SO BIG
YOU COULD EAT OATMEAL OUT OF IT.

36:05.585 --> 36:08.586
AND GET YOUR FEET OFF MY COUCH!
DO I HAVE TO TELL YOU TWICE?

36:08.588 --> 36:10.356
DO YOU WANT ME
TO WRITE IT DOWN FOR YOU?

36:10.358 --> 36:11.557
WHAT ABOUT 'SHROOMS?
YOU WANT SOME OF THOSE, TOO?

36:11.559 --> 36:12.791
[PHONE RINGING]

36:12.793 --> 36:13.995
SOMEBODY GET
THE TELEPHONE, PLEASE?

36:23.503 --> 36:24.639
[WHISTLES]
HEY!

36:25.940 --> 36:27.706
YOU THE BRAINS BEHIND
THIS OPERATION?

36:27.708 --> 36:29.675
[ALL LAUGHING]

36:29.677 --> 36:32.144
NOT HARDLY.

36:32.146 --> 36:34.512
[RUSSELL]
YOU DON'T TALK MUCH,

36:34.514 --> 36:38.717
BUT, UH, WHO ELSE WOULD YOU
RATHER RIDE WITH?

36:38.719 --> 36:41.686
- WHOO!
- HEY, YOU WATCH YOUR NECK.

36:41.688 --> 36:43.856
ALL RIGHT?

36:43.858 --> 36:46.391
SEE YOU SOON.

36:46.393 --> 36:48.962
- [ENGINE REVVING]
- SOONER THAN LATER.

36:54.934 --> 36:56.438
[HOWARD]
WHOO!

36:58.172 --> 37:00.671
DUMB-ASSES.

37:00.673 --> 37:03.941
MAN, THAT GUY'S
COOL AS HELL.

37:03.943 --> 37:05.878
WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU SAW HIM?

37:05.880 --> 37:07.579
HE'S KINDA LAYING LOW.

37:07.581 --> 37:08.783
HOW COME?

37:10.717 --> 37:12.483
IT WAS ABOUT A YEAR AGO,

37:12.485 --> 37:14.820
RUSTY CONVINCED ME TO GO SEE
SOME CHICK, TO HIS BEACH.

37:14.822 --> 37:18.490
HE WAS DRUNK AS HELL
WHEN HE PICKED ME UP.

37:18.492 --> 37:22.126
AND THREE HOURS LATER,
WE WAS BOTH GONE.

37:22.128 --> 37:24.429
HEY! HOWDY.

37:24.431 --> 37:25.664
HEY, YOU KNOW WHERE...

37:25.666 --> 37:27.699
YOU KNOW WHERE
"IT'LL DO" IS?

37:27.701 --> 37:30.568
- [LAUGHING]
- EXCUSE ME?

37:30.570 --> 37:33.671
"IT'LL DO?"
IT'S MY GIRL'S PLACE.

37:33.673 --> 37:35.740
SON, I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT,

37:35.742 --> 37:37.809
BUT I SUGGEST YOU MOVE ON.

37:37.811 --> 37:40.612
- WELL, I SUGGEST YOU...
- OH, GREAT.

37:40.614 --> 37:42.514
- THANKS FOR NOTHIN'.
- MM-HMM.

37:42.516 --> 37:45.617
YOU GONNA LET HER
TALK TO YOU LIKE THAT?

37:45.619 --> 37:48.088
YOU KNOW WHAT? NO.

37:54.862 --> 37:57.563
HEY!

37:57.565 --> 38:00.865
THAT'S RIGHT, SEE?

38:00.867 --> 38:03.534
I KNOW YOU KNOW THIS PLACE.

38:03.536 --> 38:06.104
WHAT PLACE IS THAT?

38:06.106 --> 38:09.744
MY GIRL'S HOUSE, YOU BITCH.

38:11.077 --> 38:14.581
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

38:16.784 --> 38:18.519
HEY, WHERE'S THE ACID?

38:23.791 --> 38:25.757
[WOMAN]
WATCH IT.

38:25.759 --> 38:27.059
[HOWARD] RUSTY HAD
BROUGHT A SHEET OF ACID

38:27.061 --> 38:28.726
TO SHARE WITH THE GIRLS.

38:28.728 --> 38:30.762
NOW, HE DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO WITH IT,

38:30.764 --> 38:33.865
SO HE DID WHAT ANY CLEAR
THINKING DRUNK WOULD DO.

38:33.867 --> 38:35.804
HE SHOVED THEM UP HIS ASS.

38:40.507 --> 38:42.143
[JAIL DOORS SQUEAKING]

38:44.110 --> 38:46.480
- [DOORS SHUT]
- [WOMAN] ENJOY YOURSELF.

38:50.751 --> 38:52.684
THEY NEVER FOUND THE HITS,

38:52.686 --> 38:56.822
SO THEY JUST LEFT HIM ALONE
TO SLEEP IT OFF,

38:56.824 --> 38:58.789
BUT HE WASN'T DOIN'
MUCH SLEEPIN'.

38:58.791 --> 39:00.862
[MUSIC PLAYING]

39:36.563 --> 39:38.500
WHAT YOU WRITIN'?

39:41.302 --> 39:43.834
- NOTHIN'.
- HMM? WHAT YOU WRITIN' OVER HERE?

39:43.836 --> 39:47.773
WHAT IS THIS? YOU GONNA LET
ME GRAB IT LIKE THAT, HUH?

39:47.775 --> 39:49.173
[LAUGHING]

39:49.175 --> 39:51.545
- COME ON!
- I DON'T KNOW.

39:53.646 --> 39:57.150
JUST STUFF.

40:03.222 --> 40:06.090
[LAUGHING]

40:06.092 --> 40:09.029
THAT'S FASCINATING.

40:13.833 --> 40:15.235
STUFF.

40:22.842 --> 40:26.878
♪ YOU SAID ON YOUR LETTER ♪

40:26.880 --> 40:29.017
♪ THE OTHER DAY ♪

40:30.351 --> 40:33.818
♪ YOU DON'T CARE ♪

40:33.820 --> 40:36.290
♪ IF I CRIME DON'T PAY ♪

40:37.724 --> 40:40.925
♪ YOU GOT MY GIRL ♪

40:40.927 --> 40:43.628
♪ NOW YOU DONE HER WRONG ♪

40:43.630 --> 40:44.695
OOH! HEY!

40:44.697 --> 40:45.831
HEY, BABY!

40:45.833 --> 40:47.132
YOUR MAMA LET YOU DATE?

40:47.134 --> 40:48.700
WHY DON'T YOU
GET BIT, ASSWIPE?

40:48.702 --> 40:49.871
[GIBBERING]

40:52.639 --> 40:55.072
NOW THAT'S A PIECE OF ASS.

40:55.074 --> 40:57.708
WHOA, DUDE,
WHO LET SHAMU OUT?

40:57.710 --> 41:01.278
YEAH, MAYBE SHE'D LET YOU BEND
HER LIKE A SUITCASE, HUH?

41:01.280 --> 41:05.820
- DOUBTFUL. DOUBTFUL.
- ♪ YOU GOT ME IN MISERY ♪

41:13.994 --> 41:17.762
♪ THE FBI ♪

41:17.764 --> 41:21.365
♪ IS ON YOUR TRAIL ♪

41:21.367 --> 41:24.735
♪ ELLIOT NESS ♪

41:24.737 --> 41:27.074
♪ WON'T LET YOU REST ♪

41:28.375 --> 41:32.244
♪ HAVE GUN WILL TRAVEL ♪

41:32.246 --> 41:35.780
♪ IS IN MY PAY ♪

41:35.782 --> 41:39.184
♪ HE SWEARS TO GET YOU ♪

41:39.186 --> 41:41.021
♪ IF IT TAKES ALL DAY ♪

41:52.833 --> 41:54.068
YEAH, I'M GOOD.

41:59.373 --> 42:02.043
[LAUGHING]

42:04.844 --> 42:08.412
♪ ROUTE 66 ♪

42:08.414 --> 42:12.150
♪ IS IN THE RACE ♪

42:12.152 --> 42:15.387
♪ PERRY MASON ♪

42:15.389 --> 42:18.222
♪ WILL TAKE MY CASE ♪

42:18.224 --> 42:20.758
A-WASTIN' TIME.

42:20.760 --> 42:22.429
[BOY] YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.
WHATEVER.

42:26.099 --> 42:27.402
[LAUGHING]

42:35.509 --> 42:38.211
[BOYS LAUGHING]

42:43.150 --> 42:46.150
[GIRL] LOOK, I JUST GOT A SINGLE.
THIS IS GOOD.

42:46.152 --> 42:49.354
[GIRL 2] I MEAN, YEAH,
THAT'S A GOOD IMPROVEMENT.

42:49.356 --> 42:52.126
- I JUST...
- OH, YEAH.

42:55.795 --> 42:59.498
- HE SAW ME LOOKING.
- [BOTH LAUGHING]

42:59.500 --> 43:02.266
WAY TO GO.

43:02.268 --> 43:05.202
HOW'S IT GOING?

43:05.204 --> 43:06.804
WHAT?

43:06.806 --> 43:08.108
NOTHING.

43:09.510 --> 43:12.010
I'M ALAN.

43:12.012 --> 43:13.545
WHAT?

43:13.547 --> 43:15.981
THE NAME'S ALAN.

43:15.983 --> 43:19.383
HEY, ALAN.

43:19.385 --> 43:21.286
WHAT'S SO FUNNY?

43:21.288 --> 43:24.555
NOTHING MUCH, ALAN.

43:24.557 --> 43:29.329
- I'M REBECCA.
- I'M ASIA.

43:51.885 --> 43:55.954
[JOSEPH] MY PLACE OF PEACE
WAS ALWAYS THE WATER,

43:55.956 --> 44:00.124
WHERE THE LOUD BUZZ OF FEAR
AND DOUBT WASHED AWAY,

44:00.126 --> 44:02.561
AND ALL THAT REMAINED WAS ME,

44:02.563 --> 44:04.465
PURE AS A SIMPLE STORY.

44:06.365 --> 44:10.204
[TRUMPET MUSIC]

44:14.541 --> 44:17.943
HIS HORN WAS A GIFT,
BEATS OF GRACE

44:17.945 --> 44:20.347
THAT SPRUNG FORTH
LIKE A FOUNTAIN...

44:22.382 --> 44:25.286
SOARING OVER
A SALTWATER CREEK...

44:26.887 --> 44:30.091
MADE CLOSER TO THE OCEAN
WITH EACH STRIDE.

44:36.463 --> 44:39.930
BUT WHEN THE LAST NOTE
DRIFTED DOWN AND THEN AWAY,

44:39.932 --> 44:44.101
HE WAS LEFT WITH
THE SAME DRY SORROW

44:44.103 --> 44:46.938
WHERE FEAR LURKED,

44:46.940 --> 44:49.376
AND TOUCH WAS COLD
AS MIDNIGHT.

44:53.280 --> 44:57.883
IN THOSE SMALL HOURS,
HE'D LOOK UP INTO A BLACK SEA

44:57.885 --> 45:01.286
DOTTED WITH STARS
LIKE LANTERNS ON A FOGGY SHORE

45:01.288 --> 45:04.958
LIT FOR THE LOST FISHERMAN.

45:06.927 --> 45:10.028
FIX ME.

45:10.030 --> 45:11.532
[TRUMPET MUSIC CONTINUES]

45:29.016 --> 45:32.083
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, I DO. DUDE,
THERE'S NO SHAKING THE HABIT.

45:32.085 --> 45:33.318
WHATEVER.
OH, ARE YOU...

45:33.320 --> 45:35.287
- CUTE.
- OH, ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

45:35.289 --> 45:37.389
- WHOA.
- WHAT?

45:37.391 --> 45:38.657
WATCH IT, PUNK.

45:38.659 --> 45:40.157
SORRY.

45:40.159 --> 45:41.458
YEAH, YOU'RE DAMN STRAIGHT
YOU'RE SORRY.

45:41.460 --> 45:43.330
I OUGHTA BEAT YOUR ASS.

45:45.164 --> 45:47.000
LITTLE FAGGOT.

45:49.001 --> 45:51.038
[BOY LAUGHING]

46:02.349 --> 46:07.686
♪ SAVE ME A SEAT
ON THE CAROUSEL ♪

46:07.688 --> 46:13.191
♪ PLAY ME AN OLD SONG
THAT WE LOVE SO WELL ♪

46:13.193 --> 46:18.496
♪ WE'LL KEEP ON RIDING
AROUND AND AROUND ♪

46:18.498 --> 46:22.503
♪ LIVING OUR LIFE'S
UPS AND DOWNS ♪

46:26.505 --> 46:31.642
♪ ALL OF THE CHANGES
LIFE PUTS US THROUGH ♪

46:31.644 --> 46:34.445
♪ DAMNED IF WE DON'T ♪

46:34.447 --> 46:37.081
♪ DAMNED IF WE DO ♪

46:37.083 --> 46:42.253
♪ BUT I REMAIN HOPEFUL
AND EACH NIGHT I PRAY ♪

46:42.255 --> 46:46.193
♪ THE GOOD LORD
WILL FIND A WAY ♪

46:48.394 --> 46:53.164
LOOK AT YA, A COUPLE
OF SORRY SONS OF BITCHES.

46:53.166 --> 46:55.200
[ALAN BABBLING]

46:55.202 --> 46:56.971
DUDE, GET OUTTA MY FACE.

46:58.204 --> 46:59.940
LET'S GO.

47:01.708 --> 47:03.508
[HOWARD]
WHERE WE GOING?

47:03.510 --> 47:05.079
[ALAN]
IT'S GONNA RAIN.

47:07.414 --> 47:09.713
[HOWARD, IMITATING]
IT'S GONNA RAIN.

47:09.715 --> 47:12.385
FUCKIN' WEATHER MAN
OVER THERE.

47:15.088 --> 47:17.258
[HOWARD SIGHING]

47:21.628 --> 47:23.293
KEEPIN' DRY?

47:23.295 --> 47:25.131
MY WHISTLE
SURE AS HELL IS.

47:26.333 --> 47:30.135
WHAT CAN I GET Y'ALL?

47:30.137 --> 47:32.470
THREE SHOTS OF BOURBON.

47:32.472 --> 47:34.508
[THUNDER ROLLING]

47:36.675 --> 47:38.175
